The paper deals with a model of selective prediction, which involves predicting a pre-specified statistic of an online data sequence. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the estimation of statistics of a sequence of observations, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper highlights several open directions for future work, which suggests that it may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
